            The Wall Street Journal criticized Mitt Romney's speech at the Republican National Convention this week as too vague and "failing to explain his own agenda." "If they can't confidently and aggressively win the argument for tax reform and spending restraint and why they promote faster growth and more jobs, they will give Mr. Obama an opening to win an election he should lose," the editorial said.
